  <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
  <p>These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your access to the Pacific Ocean Tech website and use of our remote staffing, talent placement, and related professional services. By using our site or engaging our services, you agree to these Terms.</p>

  <h2>Services</h2>
  <p>POT connects clients with dedicated remote professionals. We provide sourcing, vetting, onboarding support, and ongoing account management. Unless expressly stated in a Master Services Agreement (MSA) or Statement of Work (SOW), POT does not perform client work product directly—professionals are dedicated to the client under agreed terms.</p>

  <h2>Client responsibilities</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Provide accurate role requirements and lawful work assignments</li>
    <li>Maintain appropriate supervision, tools, and access for placed professionals</li>
    <li>Comply with employment, tax, and industry regulations in your jurisdiction</li>
    <li>Pay invoices per agreed schedules and rates</li>
    <li>Protect confidential information and intellectual property</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Fees and payment</h2>
  <p>Fees are specified in your order form, SOW, or proposal. Invoices are due net 15 unless otherwise agreed. Late payments may incur interest and suspension of services. Deposits or setup fees, if any, are non-refundable except as stated in your agreement.</p>

  <h2>Replacement and satisfaction</h2>
  <p>If a placed professional does not meet agreed standards within the guarantee period in your SOW, POT will provide a replacement candidate at no additional recruiting fee, subject to documented performance issues and good-faith cooperation.</p>

  <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
  <p>Work product created by dedicated professionals for the client is assigned to the client as specified in the MSA. POT retains rights to its methodologies, screening processes, training materials, and website content.</p>

  <h2>Confidentiality</h2>
  <p>Each party agrees to protect the other's confidential information and use it only for the engagement. Mutual NDAs in client agreements supplement these Terms.</p>

  <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
  <p>To the maximum extent permitted by law, POT is not liable for indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages. Our aggregate liability arising from an engagement is limited to fees paid by the client to POT in the three months preceding the claim, except for fraud or willful misconduct.</p>

  <h2>Indemnification</h2>
  <p>Clients indemnify POT against claims arising from client-provided instructions, unlawful use of services, or misuse of placed professionals. POT indemnifies clients against claims that POT's proprietary materials infringe third-party IP, subject to standard exclusions.</p>

  <h2>Termination</h2>
  <p>Either party may terminate per the notice period in the SOW. Either party may terminate for material breach not cured within 15 days of written notice. Accrued fees and confidentiality survive termination.</p>

  <h2>Governing law</h2>
  <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of India, without regard to conflict-of-law rules, unless a signed MSA specifies otherwise. Disputes shall be resolved in courts located in Chandigarh, India, subject to mandatory consumer protections where applicable.</p>

